{{setTitle     "Pure"}}
{{setSubTitle  "A set of small, responsive CSS modules that you can use in every web project."}}
{{setActiveNav "home"}}

{{addLocalCSS "/css/home.css"}}

<div class="hero">
    <h1 class="pure-u-1">{{title}}</h1>
    <h2 class="pure-u-3-4 l-centered">{{subTitle}}</h2>

    <div class="hero-cta pure-u-3-4">
    {{#code}}
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="http://yui.yahooapis.com/pure/{{pure.version}}/pure-min.css">
    {{/code}}

    <p>
        <a class="pure-button pure-button-cta" href="{{pages.customize}}">Get Started</a>
    </p>
    <p>
        <a href="https://github.com/yui/pure/">View on Github</a>
        <span class="muted">|</span>
        <span class="muted">Version {{pure.version}}</span>
    </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="pure-g-r marketing-ribbon">
    <div class="pure-u-1">
        <div class="size-chart l-vbox pure-g">
            <div class="size-chart-item size-chart-base pure-u" style="width: 25%;">
                <a class="size-chart-label" href="{{pages.base}}">
                    Base <span class="size-chart-size">(1.2KB)</span>
                </a>
            </div>
            <div class="size-chart-item size-chart-grids pure-u" style="width: 14.5%;">
                <a class="size-chart-label" href="{{pages.grids}}">
                    Grids <span class="size-chart-size">(0.7KB)</span>
                </a>
            </div>
            <div class="size-chart-item size-chart-forms pure-u"style="width: 27%;">
                <a class="size-chart-label" href="{{pages.forms}}">
                    Forms <span class="size-chart-size">(1.3KB)</span>
                </a>
            </div>
            <div class="size-chart-item size-chart-tables pure-u" style="width: 12.5%;">
                <a class="size-chart-label" href="{{pages.tables}}">
                    Tables <span class="size-chart-size">(0.6KB)</span>
                </a>
            </div>
            <div class="size-chart-item size-chart-menus pure-u" style="width: 21%;">
                <a class="size-chart-label" href="{{pages.menus}}">
                    Menus <span class="size-chart-size">(1KB)</span>
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="l-box">
            <h3>CSS with the tiniest footprint.</h3>
            <p>
                Pure is ridiculously tiny. The entire set of modules clocks in at <strong>4.8KB minified and gzipped</strong>, without forgoing responsive styles, design, or ease of use. Crafted with mobile devices in mind, it was important to us to keep our file sizes small, and every line of CSS was carefully considered. If you decide to only use a subset of these modules, you'll save even more bytes.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="pure-g-r marketing-ribbon">
    <div class="pure-u-1-3">
        <div class="l-box">
            <h3>Your CSS foundation.</h3>
            <p>
                Pure builds on <a href="http://necolas.github.io/normalize.css/" alt="Normalize.css">normalize.css</a> and provides layout and styling for native HTML elements, plus the most common UI components. It's what you need, without the cruft.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pure-u-1-3">
        <div class="l-box">
            <h3>Made with mobile in mind.</h3>
            <p>
                Pure is responsive out of the box, so elements look great on all screen sizes. Customize your styles with the <a href="http://yui.github.io/skinbuilder" alt="SkinBuilder">SkinBuilder</a> to make your style your own.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pure-u-1-3">
        <div class="l-box">
            <h3>Stays out of your way.</h3>
            <p>
                Pure has minimal styles and encourages you to write your application styles on top of it. It's designed to get out of your way and makes it easy to override styles.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


<div class="pure-g-r marketing-ribbon">
    <div class="pure-u-1-2">
        <div class="l-box">
            <a href="{{pages.layouts}}">
                <img src="img/layout-icon.jpg" alt="Diagram of a sample layout.">
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pure-u-1-2">
        <div class="l-hbox">
            <h3>Create responsive layouts.</h3>
            <p>
                By using <a href="{{pages.grids}}">Grids</a>, <a href="{{pages.lists}}">Navigation lists</a>, and more, it's easy to create beautiful responsive layouts for all screen sizes. We've made it easy for you to get started. Take a look at a few different <a href="{{pages.layouts}}">layouts</a> and start your next web project with a rock-solid foundation.
            </p>

            <p>
                <a href="{{pages.layouts}}" class="pure-button">View Layouts</a>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
